gomodel:SYNGO_2807  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: \"Wnt7a-Dvl1 signalling regulates release probability at glutamatergic synapses in the hippocampus\"\n\nFig.3: \"Acute exposure to Wnt7a increases release probability without affecting synapse number in mature hippocampal neurons\"\n\nFig.4: \"Wnt signalling regulates synaptic vesicle number\".\n\nFig.5: \"Wnt signalling regulates the RRP size\"\n\nFig.6: \"Wnt signalling regulates SNARE complex formation and Dvl1 interacts with proteins of the release machinery\"\n\nFig.7: \"Wnts modulate the interaction between Dvl1 and Syt-1\". Experimental description: - \"However, the in vivo requirement for Wnt signalling in neurotransmitter release has not been investigated. To address this issue, we examined Wnt-deficient mice lacking both Wnt7a and Dvl1 (Wnt7a; Dvl1 knock-out (KO)), as these mice exhibit a stronger phenotype than Wnt7a or Dvl1 single mutants25,28. \"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-19" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2807" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

